**wkhtmltopdf version(s) affected**: 0.12.4

**OS information**
Ubuntu Bionic

**Description**
When using wkhtmltopdf to convert an HTML page with Brandon Grotesque font (base64 encoded inline form), some characters like `C`, `G`, `O` appear slightly cut off on the left, while others like `0` appear cutoff on the bottom.

**How to reproduce**
In order to reproduce, run wkhtmltopdf with the following html page:
```html
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      p {
        width: 98mm;
        float: left;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        -moz-box-sizing: border-box;
        -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;
        padding: 0;
        display: table;
        font-family: "Brandon";
      }

      @media all {
        @font-face {
          font-family: 'Brandon';
          src:  url(data:application/font-ttf;charset=utf-8;base64,) format('truetype');
          font-weight: normal;
          font-style: normal;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
<body>
  <p>C, G, O.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

**Expected behavior**
We'd expect the characters to look the same as in its HTML form. Instead, they are cut off on a few places.

Note that when running the same example with the Mac OS X version of wkhtmltopdf, the issue disappears and the characters show as one would expect.

In order to help reproduce the issue, the following `Dockerfile` can be used:

```Dockerfile
FROM ubuntu:bionic

RUN apt-get update && apt-get -y upgrade
RUN apt-get -y install libxrender1 libfontconfig1 libxext6

RUN mkdir /app
WORKDIR /app

COPY . /app
```

Ensure you have the html page inside the the same folder (e.g. name it test.html), as well as the linux binary of wkhtmltopdf, then run this to see the pdf output:
`docker build -t wkhtmltopdf_test:latest . && docker run -v `pwd`:`pwd` -w `pwd` wkhtmltopdf_test:latest ./wkhtmltopdf-linux-amd64 test.html test.pdf`
